The paper deals with a spectrum-sharing system with interference links, which is a common topic in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The proposed solution involves the usage of an Electronically Steerable Parasitic Array Radiator (ESPAR) antenna, which is a type of antenna technology that falls under the Multimedia (cs.MM) and Architecture (cs.AR) sub-categories. Finally, the paper also discusses the analytical and numerical results of the proposed solution, which can be categorized under the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
